  <title>
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">The water we want - Salinity cripples life</narrative>
  </title>
  <description>
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">Bangladesh is one of the worst sufferers of global climate change and environmental degradation. Scarcity of safe water is a severe crisis for people living in the Sundarbans, world&apos;s largest mangrove forest. This has become a question of life and death of the villagers where all sources of surface and ground water have fast growing trend of increased salinity. &quot;The water we want&quot; fund will install small desalination plants to supply safe water to the suffering families to save their lives.</narrative>
  </description>
